.TH "pldmfw_flash_image" 9 "pldmfw_flash_image" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pldmfw_flash_image \- Write a PLDM-formatted firmware image to the device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" pldmfw_flash_image
.BI "(struct pldmfw *context "  ","
.BI "const struct firmware *fw "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "context" 12
ops and data for firmware update
.IP "fw" 12
firmware object pointing to the relevant firmware file to program
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Parse the data for a given firmware file, verifying that it is a valid PLDM
formatted image that matches this device.

Extract the device record Package Data and Component Tables and send them
to the device firmware. Extract and write the flash data for each of the
components indicated in the firmware file.
.SH "RETURN"
zero on success, or a negative error code on failure.
